         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is in two parts. Part I contains a description of the Danilewski algorithm for reducing a matrix to Frobenius form using rational arithmetic. This algorithm is modified for use over the field of integers modulo $p$. The modified algorithm yields exact integral factors of the characteristic polynomial. A description of the single-modulus algorithm is given. Part II contains a description of the multiple-modulus algorithm. Since different moduli may yield different factorizations, an algorithm is given for determining which factorizations are not correct factorizations over the integers of the characteristic polynomial.</p>
          </abstract>
